<HEADLINE>
TAIWAN WINS FIVE AWARDS IN HOUSTON FILM FESTIVAL
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dallas,   April  29  (CNA) 04/30/07  17:27:48 (By Chang Hui-yen
and Nick Huang)
</P>
<P>
Taiwan  took five awards at the just-concluded 40th Worldfest-
Houston International Film Festival, Taiwan's representative
office in Houston said over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The winning films included Amour-Legende by director Wu Mi-sen;
Visions of Taiwan's Mountains and Digitized Operations in Taiwan
-- both of which are documentaries made by the Government
Information Office -- and Kuanwu Formosan Salamander and Taipei
MRT -- both directed by Chen Chin-fa.
</P>
<P>
Amour-Legende is a story about a young man who suffers from
memory loss and begins to question his own existence after going
on a journey to a remote island.
</P>
<P>
The film was shown at the 2006 Taipei Golden Horse Film Festival
and won the Global Vision Award in the 31st Hong Kong
International Film Festival held March 20-April 11.
</P>
<P>
Chen's Kuanwu Formosan Salamander deals with an endangered
species of amphibian endemic to the Kuanwu area in the northern
Taiwan county of Miaoli.
</P>
<P>
Chen, who has been dedicated to ecological conservation for 18
years, has made many documentaries on endangered species in
Taiwan.
</P>
